<TITLE>Kirk, Virginia Pauline Hayes</TITLE>
<TEXT>
, after a short illness, an angel entered Heaven as Virginia Pauline Kirk, age 73, went home to be with her Lord and Savior. Pauline was born in Smyth County, Va. to the late James S. and Demma Osborne Hayes and was preceded in death by her brothers, Bill, Bob, Rush and Roy Hayes; sisters, Robena Jo Hayes and Dorothy Jane Mays. She made her home in Catlet, Va. for over 46 years and was a graduate of Sugar Grove High School, class of 1963. She was an employee of Walmart in Warrenton, Va. where she worked as a people greeter. She was a member of the Auburn Baptist Church and was devoted wife, mother, grandmother and sister who will be missed dearly. She had many friends and was loved by everyone, all of whom showed how much during her illness. She was an extraordinary person. Virginia or Pauline, which ever name you may know her by, is survived by her loving husband, George Kirk, best known as Red; her son, Michael Kirk; granddaughter, Emily Kirk; grandson, Owen Kirk all of Catlett, Va.; her sisters, Mary Dutton, Leesburg, Shirley Powers and husband, Junior, Marion, Stella Maharg, Newark, Ohio, Irene Wyatt and husband, John, Marion, Judy Hopkins, Marion; many nieces and nephews. Funeral services will be held Monday, January 30, 2017, at 11 a.m. at the Valley View Baptist Church with Pastors Lee Carpenter, Roger Frost and Paul Kirk officiating. Interment will follow in Kirk Cemetery. The family will receive friends on Sunday, January 29, 2017, from 6 to 8 p.m. at the Bradley's Funeral Home or any time at the home of Fran Hayes. In lieu of flowers, memorial contributions can be made to St. Judes Children's Hospital. Expressions of sympathy may be sent to the family at www.bradleysfh.com . Bradley's Funeral Home is serving the Kirk family. 
